  "text": "Enzyme activity is also temperature dependent, and each enzyme has an optimum temperature range where its activity is greatest. Inhibition of enzyme activity could be another reason explaining the reduction in anthocyanin biosynthesis . For example, UFGT activity could be maintained or even increased at higher temperature, and anthocyanin biosynthesis could be maintained as highlighted in the in vitro study of [CITATION_1] .",
